    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/7747</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-03T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7129. Embassy’s 9232, March 27, 11 a.m. It is impracticable and unwise to apply
                    the test of trading with enemy firms to reputable neutral firms in Scandinavian
                    countries. Pending the publication of our enemy trading list for neutral Europe,
                    the British and French lists should be adopted as the guide to the character of
                    the firms concerned and our practice in approving or refusing applications to
                    export to Scandinavian houses other than those shown on such lists will be
                    determined by our representative in London, who will be in touch with the
                    practice of the British and French licensing authorities. Evidence indicating
                    the desirability of additions to or removals from the lists should be reported
                    to London and Washington after conference with Allied colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
